BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:identiverse-2025-PersonalIdentityWorkshop-20250603-767cb0e9@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20250314T160835Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20250603T093000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20250603T113000
SUMMARY:Personal Identity Workshop (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:Traditional identity models often fail to balance security with user autono
 my, leading to over-reliance on centralized data, privacy risks, and fricti
 on in digital experiences. This workshop explores the evolution of personal
  identity, focusing on decentralized identity, self-sovereign identity (SSI
 ), and verifiable credentials. Attendees will learn how to navigate the shi
 ft toward user-controlled identity models while ensuring compliance, securi
 ty, and interoperability in a rapidly evolving landscape.

Speakers: Christ
 ine Owen Field, CTO 1Kosmos Christine Owen Teresa Wu Vice President, Smart 
 Credentials & Access IDEMIA Public Security Teresa Wu

Session Type: WORKSH
 OP

All times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC-7)
LOCATION:Mandalay Bay D
CLASS:PUBLIC
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:OPAQUE
