UID:identiverse-2025-ContinuousIdentityWorkshop-20250603-15592008@identiverse.com
SEQUENCE:0
DTSTAMP:20250314T160835Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20250603T093000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20250603T113000
SUMMARY:Continuous Identity Workshop (PDT)
DESCRIPTION:This workshop introduces event-driven and continuous identity approaches, e
 xploring standards such as CAEP, RISC, and Shared Signals. Security archite
 ctures need to be designed to be more intentional with an “Identity First” 
 perspective and proactive threat detection capabilities.  Through discussio
 ns on the current limitations and future possibilities, attendees will disc
 over how to prepare their systems for an evolving identity landscape while 
 minimizing risks and improving accuracy.

Speakers: Andrew Cameron Technica
 l Fellow, IAM General Motors Andrew Cameron Sean O’Dell Senior Staff Securi
 ty Engineer, Consumer and Workforce IAM The Walt Disney Company Sean O’Dell
 

Session Type: WORKSHOP

All times are in Pacific Daylight Time (PDT / UTC
 -7)
